WEBVTT


00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:03.540
The three most elite National Guard units in the USA.

00:00:03.720 --> 00:00:06.040
No. 3 Pennsylvania National Guard.

00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:08.400
With a budget of around $200 million

00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:10.400
and around 19,000 members,

00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:14.840
they possess a notable fleet of AH64 Apache helicopters,

00:00:14.840 --> 00:00:18.040
providing them with formidable air support capabilities.

00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:20.400
Their rigorous cold weather training programs

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:21.840
in the states diverse terrain

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:24.680
ensure unmatched readiness for various climates.

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:27.960
No. 2 California The California National Guard

00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:30.200
stands out for its technological prowess,

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:31.920
integrating cutting edge surveillance

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:33.380
and communication systems.

00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:36.760
With a strength of approximately 18,000 personnel,

00:00:36.760 --> 00:00:40.120
they uniquely operate a fleet of MQ9 Reaper drones

00:00:40.120 --> 00:00:42.160
for both domestic and overseas missions.

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:44.180
A testament to their innovative approach.

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:45.680
Before revealing the number one,

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:47.960
remember to subscribe and like the video.

00:00:47.960 --> 00:00:50.080
No. 1 Texas National Guard

00:00:50.080 --> 00:00:52.920
with an annual budget exceeding $300 million,

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:53.960
Texas boasts

00:00:53.960 --> 00:00:56.600
the largest National Guard contingent in the US

00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:58.600
with over 25,000 members.

00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:01.040
It's renowned for its advanced military equipment,

00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:04.800
including M1 Abrams tanks and F16 fighter jets.

00:01:04.800 --> 00:01:06.760
Their annual training exercises,

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:08.960
often involving complex simulations,

00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:11.708
set a high standard for guard units nationwide.
